<p>evening... <br /> <br />i recently started a bard and lvld him to lvl 20(had to go to dentist or i woulda played longer).&nbsp;&nbsp;He has better than average equipment and -could- be called twinked, although i doubt he hads top-notch gear.  The problem ive run into is exp.  ive hit a wall.  OT is too tough, as it takes too long to kill and the mobs are few and far between.  PC isnt tough enough as all i can find are blues, and not enough of them at a time to fufill my appetite.  My question is this:   are there intermediate zones to hunt in? (say unrest, LoIO, or the like)  below is where i hunted/where i plan on hunting.  any advise is greatly appreciated. <br /> <br /> <br />lvl 1-5  -- orc hill, gfay <br />lvl 5-10ish -- CB, pref in the castle <br />lvl 10-20 -- PC <br />lvl 20-35 -- OT <br />lvl 35-45 -- DL,gunthak,dulak <br />lvl 45-51 -- dulak boats <br /> <br />Thanks in Advance <br />Zaon Theaeon <br />^65cleric <br />Intermisceo Perfectus <br />^20 bard <br />The Rathe</p>
