		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.44]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>20-25 - Paludal Caverns. Either group at bandit camps or solo on the backside. <br /> <br />26-27 - Fear kite gnolls at the spires in South Karana or Tizmaks in Great Divide. Gnolls will be quite a bit easier. <br /> <br />27-30 - Swarm kite or charm kite gnolls in SK.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />30-40 - Swarm kite cougars in Iceclad Ocean. Chant the few that are too high for your 27 charm (or use them for pet fodder) until you get your 39 charm. <br />   <br />(or) <br /> <br />30-45 - Swarm kite spirocs in Timorous Deep. Just watch for the new rogue epic 2.0 spawns near the mountain. <br /> <br />45-50 - Swarm in Dulaks if you can handle it. That may take some trial and error. <br /> <br />50+ - Swarm Nightstalkers in Plane of Nightmare or rats/flies in Plane of Disease. Eventually you could move on to kiting sentries in Halls of Honor also. <br /> <br />This being said, I highly suggest you group as much as possible. It's important to learn how to pull for a group, not just yourself, as well as how to handle crowd control as a bard. Even if you've played a chanter to higher levels before, CC is completely different as a bard. Also, work on your defense every once in a while. If you only kite, you're going to end up at level 65 with 150 in defense, and that would suck.</p>
